WEBVTT

00:00.767 --> 00:04.470
♪

00:04.472 --> 00:06.538
<i>Fluttershy: Ok,</i>
<i>everypony, as you know,</i>

00:06.540 --> 00:09.408
The adorable fairy
creatures known as breezies

00:09.410 --> 00:11.510
Are about to come
through ponyville.

00:11.512 --> 00:14.279
Yes! It's so exciting!

00:14.281 --> 00:16.782
I can't wait for rainbow dash
to make the breeze for them

00:16.784 --> 00:19.418
So I can see how cute
they are up close!

00:19.420 --> 00:21.120
I've never done it before.

00:21.122 --> 00:23.122
Not that I won't be
totally awesome at it.

00:23.124 --> 00:24.623
Because I totally will.

00:24.625 --> 00:26.692
And that breeze
is very important.

00:26.694 --> 00:29.628
But so is cheering on those
teeny, tiny little things

00:29.630 --> 00:31.630
So they have the confidence
to ride that breeze

00:31.632 --> 00:33.265
To their native land.

00:33.267 --> 00:35.200
Did I mention how tiny they are?

00:35.202 --> 00:36.235
So tiny.

00:37.537 --> 00:41.073
I was thinking we could do
a special breezy cheer.

00:41.075 --> 00:43.475
I love cheers!

00:43.477 --> 00:46.245
But these cheers
should be quiet cheers.

00:46.247 --> 00:47.579
We don't want to
startle them.

00:47.581 --> 00:50.049
They need to be
able to concentrate.

00:50.051 --> 00:51.750
Why don't we try it?

00:51.752 --> 00:53.786
You can do it, breezies.

00:53.788 --> 00:56.088
You can do it, breezies!

00:56.090 --> 00:57.423
Oh my.

00:57.425 --> 01:00.159
Sorry, fluttershy, I had
no idea how hard it was

01:00.161 --> 01:02.761
To do a cheer quietly.

01:02.763 --> 01:06.331
It's ok. Quiet doesn't come
naturally for everypony.

01:06.333 --> 01:07.699
Let's try it again.

01:07.701 --> 01:10.536
You can do it, breezies!

01:10.538 --> 01:13.439
Perhaps just a
little bit quieter.

01:13.441 --> 01:16.308
You can do it, breezies!

01:16.310 --> 01:17.776
Just a little quieter.

01:17.778 --> 01:20.579
(whispered)
you can do it, breezies!

01:20.581 --> 01:21.680
Perfect!

01:22.649 --> 01:24.783
Oh, um, I mean...Yay.

01:28.221 --> 01:31.056
<i>♪ my little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:31.058 --> 01:33.058
<i>♪ aaaaahhh!</i>

01:33.060 --> 01:34.093
<i>♪ (upbeat)</i>

01:34.095 --> 01:36.261
<i>♪ my little pony</i>

01:36.263 --> 01:38.430
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be ♪</i>

01:38.432 --> 01:40.365
<i>♪ my little pony</i>

01:40.367 --> 01:42.568
<i>♪ until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me ♪</i>

01:42.570 --> 01:43.735
<i>♪ big adventure</i>

01:43.737 --> 01:45.070
<i>♪ tons of fun.</i>

01:45.072 --> 01:46.038
<i>♪ a beautiful heart</i>

01:46.040 --> 01:47.106
<i>♪ faithful and strong</i>

01:47.108 --> 01:48.207
<i>♪ sharing kindness</i>

01:48.209 --> 01:51.143
<i>♪ and magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete ♪</i>

01:51.145 --> 01:53.278
<i>♪ my little ponies</i>

01:53.280 --> 01:56.348
<i>♪ do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:56.350 --> 01:58.117
♪

02:03.623 --> 02:08.260
♪

02:08.262 --> 02:11.230
<i>♪ (mariachi band)</i>

02:11.232 --> 02:16.034
♪

02:16.036 --> 02:20.105
<i>(whistling wind)</i>

02:20.107 --> 02:22.441
That's too strong!

02:22.443 --> 02:24.243
We've gotta slow
this breeze down

02:24.245 --> 02:26.478
Or we're going to blow
those breezies apart!

02:29.149 --> 02:31.416
What I don't understand is
why they need the pegasi

02:31.418 --> 02:33.218
To make a breeze for them.

02:33.220 --> 02:35.320
Well, you see,
it's the breeze

02:35.322 --> 02:37.556
That activates the
breezie's magic.

02:37.558 --> 02:40.058
And that magic protects the
pollen they're carrying

02:40.060 --> 02:41.660
From being destroyed.

02:41.662 --> 02:46.165
So no breeze means no magic
means the pollen goes bad?

02:46.167 --> 02:49.801
And they only have two days
to get that pollen back

02:49.803 --> 02:52.604
Before the portal to
their home closes.

02:52.606 --> 02:54.573
That's why it's
ever so important

02:54.575 --> 02:57.743
That we help them make their
way through ponyville safely.

02:57.745 --> 02:59.511
We certainly wouldn't
want to scare them

02:59.513 --> 03:01.513
And divert them from their path!

03:01.515 --> 03:03.482
Now you understand.

03:03.484 --> 03:05.450
You certainly know
a lot about them.

03:05.452 --> 03:07.119
Oh, thank you.

03:07.121 --> 03:09.054
I went to see them
gathering their pollen

03:09.056 --> 03:10.389
In western equestria.

03:14.227 --> 03:17.262
<i>♪ (majestic)</i>

03:17.264 --> 03:20.199
Um, rarity, I hate
to weigh in with you

03:20.201 --> 03:22.701
When it comes to fashion, but--

03:22.703 --> 03:25.237
There's too much
purple on this, isn't there?

03:25.239 --> 03:26.672
I knew it!

03:26.674 --> 03:28.574
But twilight
refused to admit it.

03:28.576 --> 03:30.108
What? I--

03:30.110 --> 03:32.244
Fluttershy: No, no. It's the
perfect amount of purple.

03:32.246 --> 03:36.048
It's just that there's an awful
lot of sequins on your jacket.

03:36.050 --> 03:40.052
Oh, darling, please! One can
never have too many sequins.

03:41.121 --> 03:45.257
And the light catches a group of
breezies right in their eyes

03:45.259 --> 03:47.626
And blinds them long enough to
get them off their course

03:47.628 --> 03:49.228
So they never get home!

03:49.230 --> 03:50.429
I stand corrected.

03:50.431 --> 03:52.231
I suppose there is
the rare instance

03:52.233 --> 03:54.199
Where one can have
too many sequins.

03:54.201 --> 03:55.601
I'll just take
off my jacket.

03:55.603 --> 03:57.703
<i>♪ (angelic chorus)</i>

03:57.705 --> 03:59.671
I suppose this won't do either.

04:08.414 --> 04:10.515
(quietly) everypony, it's time!

04:10.517 --> 04:13.252
Please welcome the breezies!

04:13.254 --> 04:24.730
♪

04:24.732 --> 04:28.367
They're as cute as apple
bloom on the day she was born!

04:28.369 --> 04:30.435
And would you look at those
adorable little packs

04:30.437 --> 04:32.738
They carry their pollen in.

04:32.740 --> 04:35.440
<i>(high-pitched gibberish</i>
<i>giving an order)</i>

04:35.442 --> 04:36.775
So! Cute!

04:36.777 --> 04:38.744
Can't! Take! It!

04:48.321 --> 04:49.321
<i>(growl)</i>

04:49.323 --> 04:53.692
Pinkie pie! Can I hop on you
so I can see the breezies?

04:53.694 --> 04:55.460
May! Explode!

04:58.231 --> 04:59.197
<i>(thud)</i>

05:04.137 --> 05:07.139
<i>(boing boing boing)</i>

05:07.141 --> 05:09.574
<i>(wind whistles)</i>

05:09.576 --> 05:11.176
Oh no!

05:11.178 --> 05:13.445
<i>(wind whistles)</i>

05:17.183 --> 05:20.118
(high-pitched panicked squeals)

05:20.120 --> 05:21.720
<i>(horrified gasp from all)</i>

05:21.722 --> 05:25.490
Slow down the breeze for
the other group to catch up!

05:25.492 --> 05:30.062
We can't connect the breeze
to both sets of breezies!

05:30.064 --> 05:31.530
What if we speed it up?

05:31.532 --> 05:33.999
Then the first group
will be going too fast

05:34.001 --> 05:35.767
And will get separated
from each other!

05:37.670 --> 05:40.038
<i>(screams)</i>

05:43.176 --> 05:49.281
<i>(frightened screams)</i>

05:49.283 --> 05:52.751
<i>(shouting orders)</i>

05:52.753 --> 05:56.355
<i>(frightened squeals)</i>

05:56.357 --> 05:57.289
<i>(gasp)</i>

06:07.734 --> 06:09.401
<i>Manglemarsh mooth!</i>

06:09.403 --> 06:13.105
You must all gather as
close as you possibly can!

06:15.541 --> 06:20.045
<i>(cheers)</i>

06:20.047 --> 06:23.115
<i>(squeaky cheers)</i>

06:23.117 --> 06:25.050
Muggledy sarken dose?

06:25.052 --> 06:29.054
Oh. I understand the language
of all kinds of creatures.

06:29.056 --> 06:30.689
You must be so proud.

06:30.691 --> 06:33.024
And you speak my language, too?

06:33.026 --> 06:36.027
<u>I</u> can. This lot can
only understand you.

06:36.029 --> 06:39.030
Clearly, they're not the
brightest bunch around.

06:39.032 --> 06:41.466
<i>(protesting squeals)</i>

06:41.468 --> 06:44.269
That...Was...Amazing!

06:44.271 --> 06:46.138
I'm sorry we couldn't
get a breeze going

06:46.140 --> 06:48.173
That would get them
back to the others.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.742
Oh, it's not your fault.

06:50.744 --> 06:53.278
I for one am very proud
of you, fluttershy.

06:53.280 --> 06:55.213
Leaping into action
like that.

06:55.215 --> 06:58.183
I feel like I should design
you a special hero's gown.

06:58.185 --> 07:01.686
Or a sash. At least a sash.

07:01.688 --> 07:06.024
I know what you're all thinking.
Why don't you just say it?

07:06.026 --> 07:08.460
I'm sorry! (sobbing)

07:08.462 --> 07:10.228
<i>This is all my fault!</i>

07:10.230 --> 07:13.064
I'm so, so sorry!

07:13.066 --> 07:15.167
Oh, spike, it's ok.

07:15.169 --> 07:17.235
It could have happened
to any one of us.

07:18.971 --> 07:21.373
Ok. Thank you!

07:21.375 --> 07:23.508
(angry squeaks)

07:23.510 --> 07:26.678
Uh, I'm just going to
stay over here.

07:26.680 --> 07:29.481
So fluttershy, you want us to
get the breeze going again

07:29.483 --> 07:31.550
So these little guys
can get a move on?

07:31.552 --> 07:34.653
<i>(clamouring)</i>

07:34.655 --> 07:37.255
Maybe we should wait
just a moment or so.

07:37.257 --> 07:39.090
They've been through so much.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.694
Just give me the word when
you think they're ready.

07:46.365 --> 07:58.343
♪

07:58.345 --> 08:01.112
Oh my, twirly, you look
like you need a blanket.

08:03.950 --> 08:04.649
Sampkin.

08:04.651 --> 08:05.951
No problem.

08:07.153 --> 08:08.420
Melanky?

08:08.422 --> 08:10.555
Oh. Did you need
some more water?

08:13.359 --> 08:15.327
<i>(slurp)</i>

08:15.329 --> 08:19.097
Now who else needed a
hoof-knitted sweater?

08:19.099 --> 08:21.199
<i>(clamouring)</i>

08:21.201 --> 08:22.200
Hey there!

08:22.202 --> 08:23.134
Can we come in?

08:23.136 --> 08:24.569
Oh, of course.

08:24.571 --> 08:25.670
But watch your step.

08:26.706 --> 08:28.607
Oops. Sorry about
that little one.

08:28.609 --> 08:31.309
We just wanted to see if you
thought the breezies were ready

08:31.311 --> 08:33.044
To give it another try.

08:33.046 --> 08:34.312
Has it been an hour already?

08:34.314 --> 08:37.415
Time flies when you're making
sure little creatures

08:37.417 --> 08:39.084
Don't feel that you're
abandoning them

08:39.086 --> 08:40.485
<i>To the cruel world.</i>

08:42.054 --> 08:45.056
But they're not going
to a cruel world, right?

08:45.058 --> 08:46.424
They're going home.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.329
Oh yes! That's right.

08:51.331 --> 08:54.432
<i>(clamouring)</i>

08:54.434 --> 08:56.234
On second thought.

08:56.236 --> 08:58.169
I don't think
they're quite ready.

08:58.171 --> 09:04.242
Marshkin pupskin larfer!
Farclop pannywafer!

09:04.244 --> 09:06.511
Uh, what did he say?

09:06.513 --> 09:09.347
I'd rather not say.

09:09.349 --> 09:12.517
Ok, well, I'm sure you
know what you're doing.

09:12.519 --> 09:15.420
No one knows rare magical
creatures like you do.

09:15.422 --> 09:16.688
We'll just wait for your word.

09:16.690 --> 09:17.689
Thank you.

09:17.691 --> 09:19.257
I'll be in touch very soon.

09:19.259 --> 09:20.559
<i>(door closes)</i>

09:20.561 --> 09:24.029
We need to go now or
we will never get home!

09:24.031 --> 09:26.231
I wish we did not need
that stupid breeze

09:26.233 --> 09:27.699
To activate our magic

09:27.701 --> 09:31.236
Or I would just force you
all to fly home right now!

09:31.238 --> 09:34.239
Why do we have to need magic
to keep our pollen safe?

09:34.241 --> 09:35.674
Now seabreeze--

09:35.676 --> 09:38.043
Why are you giving
in to these wimps?

09:38.045 --> 09:40.512
If they had not been so
scared in the first place,

09:40.514 --> 09:42.981
This never would have happened!

09:42.983 --> 09:45.450
Well, that is just
not true, seabreeze.

09:45.452 --> 09:49.020
It was because of a
leaf and you know that.

09:49.022 --> 09:50.488
Oh, please!

09:50.490 --> 09:53.458
They have no idea what
they're doing out there!

09:53.460 --> 09:56.995
Like you said, we need as
much time as we can get,

09:56.997 --> 09:59.397
Because they are so incompetent!

09:59.399 --> 10:03.368
Well, I didn't say that
exactly, now did I?

10:03.370 --> 10:05.236
(angry) huh!

10:05.238 --> 10:08.173
Oh, well, maybe a snack
will lighten the mood.

10:08.175 --> 10:10.642
<i>(excited chatter)</i>

10:10.644 --> 10:18.249
<i>♪</i>

10:18.251 --> 10:19.084
<i>(little burp)</i>

10:19.086 --> 10:20.085
Munfarzen.

10:20.087 --> 10:21.219
You're excused.

10:23.656 --> 10:26.458
Well, my breezies? I
think we can all agree

10:26.460 --> 10:29.027
That now that you've eaten and
you have a little energy

10:29.029 --> 10:30.462
Going in your breezy bodies,

10:30.464 --> 10:33.498
You're strong enough
to face the breeze!

10:33.500 --> 10:36.368
I've loved having you here and
I hope I've made you all feel

10:36.370 --> 10:37.669
Loved and special.

10:37.671 --> 10:41.139
But you have to go; no
pony here will deny that.

10:41.141 --> 10:44.409
<i>Seabreeze: There is nothing</i>
<i>special about these losers!</i>

10:44.411 --> 10:47.412
They cannot handle a
simple breeze home!

10:47.414 --> 10:51.182
If they could just stick with
the program and listen to me,

10:51.184 --> 10:54.219
We would be safe! At home!

10:54.221 --> 10:57.722
Home! Where everybreezie
is like us!

11:04.764 --> 11:06.731
<i>(sigh)</i>

11:06.733 --> 11:09.034
Ok. Well.

11:09.036 --> 11:11.169
A confusing pep talk,
but nonetheless,

11:11.171 --> 11:13.238
I do know that if you
don't leave soon,

11:13.240 --> 11:16.307
You may never make it back
and that would be terrible.

11:18.277 --> 11:19.344
Achoo!

11:19.346 --> 11:20.578
Multy marshkin follow.

11:22.748 --> 11:24.115
<i>(cough cough)</i>

11:24.117 --> 11:26.551
Multy marskin toomba too.

11:26.553 --> 11:29.020
I had no idea you
all have colds!

11:29.022 --> 11:31.322
Really? All of you?

11:31.324 --> 11:33.491
<i>(coughing)</i>

11:33.493 --> 11:36.127
Oh dear. I can't let you
go out there sick!

11:36.129 --> 11:39.197
What kind of a friend would
I be if I made you go now?

11:39.199 --> 11:43.268
<i>(excited chatter)</i>

11:43.270 --> 11:46.271
<i>(angry gibberish)</i>

11:52.344 --> 11:53.712
<i>(knock knock knock)</i>

11:53.714 --> 11:57.282
Just wondering if the
breezies are ready to go yet.

11:57.284 --> 11:59.451
Clock's kind of ticking
for them to make it back

11:59.453 --> 12:01.086
Before the door
closes on their home.

12:01.088 --> 12:03.521
Oh yes. I mean, not quite.

12:03.523 --> 12:05.356
Um, maybe just a
few more minutes?

12:05.358 --> 12:07.125
<i>(door closes)</i>

12:07.127 --> 12:09.027
Uh... All right.

12:09.029 --> 12:11.029
We wait too much longer,
we'll have to create

12:11.031 --> 12:14.165
Such a strong breeze it may
be more than they can handle.

12:14.167 --> 12:16.634
We just have to
trust fluttershy.

12:16.636 --> 12:18.403
She must know what
she's doing.

12:19.605 --> 12:22.340
<i>(happy chatter)</i>

12:22.342 --> 12:33.785
♪

12:33.787 --> 12:35.053
<i>(clatter)</i>

12:36.722 --> 12:38.490
All: Awwww!

12:38.492 --> 12:41.025
Why are you spending
your time on this?

12:41.027 --> 12:42.660
I will never get home!

12:44.263 --> 12:46.664
Breezies, I must say,
seabreeze has a point.

12:46.666 --> 12:49.534
I think it's time for me to get
rainbow dash and her friends

12:49.536 --> 12:52.103
So they can create the breeze
for you to get home.

12:52.105 --> 12:55.373
<i>(protests)</i>

12:55.375 --> 12:58.409
Oh. You're all awfully anxious.

12:58.411 --> 13:00.311
I don't want you
to feel abandoned

13:00.313 --> 13:03.982
Or that I wasn't the most kind
host I could possibly be.

13:03.984 --> 13:05.483
Doshin bafin dorm.

13:05.485 --> 13:08.219
Yes, that does make sense.

13:08.221 --> 13:09.654
Seabreeze, do you
think you could wait

13:09.656 --> 13:11.456
<i>Just a couple more hours?</i>

13:14.393 --> 13:17.428
Seabreeze? Seabreeze!

13:17.430 --> 13:19.264
Has anypony seen seabreeze?

13:29.175 --> 13:31.176
(gasp) where is he going?

13:31.178 --> 13:33.745
There's no way he can handle
being out there on his own!

13:36.782 --> 13:40.251
<i>(whistling wind)</i>

13:40.253 --> 13:43.755
<i>(panicked shouts)</i>

13:47.359 --> 13:50.762
<i>(frightened gibberish)</i>

13:52.264 --> 13:53.498
<i>(crash)</i>

13:53.500 --> 13:54.432
<i>(crash)</i>

13:54.434 --> 13:57.502
<i>(panicked shouts</i>

13:57.504 --> 13:59.504
<i>(buzzing)</i>

14:10.115 --> 14:11.249
<i>(pop)</i>

14:11.251 --> 14:12.283
<i>(scared squeals)</i>

14:12.285 --> 14:14.452
<i>(buzzing)</i>

14:14.454 --> 14:17.188
<i>(panicked shouts)</i>

14:21.994 --> 14:23.094
<i>Fluttershy: Excuse me, bees?</i>

14:24.463 --> 14:26.431
Can you please back
off my breezy friend?

14:26.433 --> 14:27.632
He didn't mean any harm.

14:27.634 --> 14:29.167
It was just an accident.

14:31.670 --> 14:33.404
I'm working on a bee type dance

14:33.406 --> 14:35.039
<i>And was hoping you</i>
<i>could help me.</i>

14:35.041 --> 14:37.308
<i>Does this bring to mind</i>
<i>any images for you?</i>

14:37.310 --> 14:39.310
<i>Perhaps a bee?</i>

14:39.312 --> 14:41.145
<i>(buzzing gets louder)</i>

14:41.147 --> 14:47.252
I have done nothing but be kind,
but I guess that is not working!

14:47.254 --> 14:49.787
You bees know better than
to hurt a helpless breezie!

14:49.789 --> 14:54.359
I demand that you go away now
or you'll have to answer to me!

14:58.797 --> 15:00.031
Mankylin!

15:00.033 --> 15:03.167
Thank you. Thank you so much.

15:03.169 --> 15:05.470
Thank you for coming after me.

15:05.472 --> 15:07.038
<i>Of course!</i>

15:07.040 --> 15:09.540
You could have gotten
seriously hurt out there!

15:09.542 --> 15:12.210
Ponyville is much too
dangerous for you!

15:12.212 --> 15:14.479
One tiny acorn is a threat!

15:14.481 --> 15:16.080
Yeah! I know.

15:16.082 --> 15:17.582
That is one reason why

15:17.584 --> 15:21.185
I have been trying to get us
to go from the beginning!

15:21.187 --> 15:22.720
Oh my goodness.

15:22.722 --> 15:26.190
I was just trying not to
hurt any creature's feelings,

15:26.192 --> 15:29.594
But my displays of kindness
may have cost you everything!

15:29.596 --> 15:33.097
Time is running out and
you may never make it home!

15:33.099 --> 15:36.134
That is exactly what I have
been telling all of them,

15:36.136 --> 15:38.202
But they do not listen to me.

15:38.204 --> 15:40.672
No breezie
ever listens to me.

15:42.408 --> 15:45.643
Seabreeze, I understand
your feelings are hurt,

15:45.645 --> 15:48.179
But it's hard for them to hear
you when you're shouting

15:48.181 --> 15:49.414
And being mean.

15:49.416 --> 15:51.683
The message doesn't get across.

15:51.685 --> 15:54.185
But what about those bees?

15:54.187 --> 15:56.454
You were not nice to them

15:56.456 --> 15:59.424
And that was the only
way they listened.

15:59.426 --> 16:02.293
Yes, but they had to go.

16:02.295 --> 16:04.629
And they wouldn't listen
to me any other way.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.737
We need to go. Now!

16:14.506 --> 16:19.143
<i>(whistling wind)</i>

16:19.145 --> 16:20.244
<i>(skid)</i>

16:22.715 --> 16:24.449
<i>My dear breezies,</i>

16:24.451 --> 16:27.318
I had to rescue seabreeze
from serious harm.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.654
And now I know more than
ever that you must leave

16:29.656 --> 16:31.356
Before it's too late.

16:31.358 --> 16:33.391
You would never
survive in ponyville.

16:35.160 --> 16:37.495
Mulshy barfin gorfis.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.564
I can't help you anymore!

16:39.566 --> 16:43.534
In fact, I wasn't helping
you at all by being nice.

16:43.536 --> 16:46.604
But the truth of the matter
is that I must be firm!

16:49.241 --> 16:50.708
You must go.

16:50.710 --> 16:51.776
Now!

16:58.784 --> 17:02.487
<i>(sniff sniff whimper)</i>

17:02.489 --> 17:03.654
<i>(door closes)</i>

17:10.396 --> 17:12.563
It's too strong!

17:12.565 --> 17:14.365
I can't do it any lighter!

17:15.401 --> 17:17.301
Neither can I!

17:17.303 --> 17:20.438
Fly back! I'm going to try and
see if I can slow it down!

17:25.978 --> 17:27.612
Now it's too light!

17:27.614 --> 17:29.347
This will never get them home!

17:32.184 --> 17:35.086
Oh my. Maybe it's because
there are too few of them.

17:35.088 --> 17:37.255
When they started their
journey there was more of them

17:37.257 --> 17:39.190
To face the breeze together.

17:39.192 --> 17:40.725
I've been studying
an old spell book

17:40.727 --> 17:42.627
From the castle of
the two sisters.

17:42.629 --> 17:45.063
There's a spell that
I think could help us.

17:45.065 --> 17:47.565
This is probably going to
feel a little funny at first,

17:47.567 --> 17:49.500
But you're going to
have to trust me.

17:51.303 --> 17:54.338
I love new ideas that make
me feel funny at first!

17:55.607 --> 17:57.475
<i>(zap)</i>

17:57.477 --> 17:59.043
<i>(gasps)</i>

17:59.045 --> 18:04.148
<i>(zaps)</i>

18:04.150 --> 18:05.283
<i>(poof)</i>

18:06.618 --> 18:07.552
<i>(pop)</i>

18:09.054 --> 18:10.188
<i>(poof)</i>

18:11.990 --> 18:12.990
Whoo!

18:12.992 --> 18:13.391
<i>(poof)</i>

18:13.393 --> 18:14.292
<i>(giggle)</i>

18:15.627 --> 18:16.527
<i>(poof)</i>

18:16.529 --> 18:26.003
♪

18:26.005 --> 18:27.505
Marful fly bartontook.

18:29.074 --> 18:30.608
Um, I mean, let's go.

18:30.610 --> 18:43.421
♪

18:43.423 --> 18:45.990
<i>(whistling wind)</i>

18:45.992 --> 18:53.431
♪

18:53.433 --> 18:54.665
Marshkin parskin.

18:54.667 --> 18:56.033
Mikar.

18:56.035 --> 18:57.635
You can do this.

18:57.637 --> 19:00.171
I am sorry for how I
treated you before.

19:00.173 --> 19:02.406
It was not right that
I called you names.

19:02.408 --> 19:05.042
I did not even really believe
those things I said.

19:05.044 --> 19:07.945
I was worried we would never
get back to our home,

19:07.947 --> 19:09.213
And I lashed out.

19:11.350 --> 19:13.317
I know you can do this.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.019
I believe in you.

19:16.421 --> 19:19.023
Hold onto me, let us
join the group.

19:19.025 --> 19:24.262
♪

19:24.264 --> 19:26.998
<i>(rushing water)</i>

19:27.000 --> 19:37.308
♪

19:37.310 --> 19:37.675
<i>(gasps)</i>

19:37.677 --> 19:42.513
♪

19:42.515 --> 19:45.049
Holy mini-sized paradise!

19:45.051 --> 19:47.618
This is simply beautiful!

19:47.620 --> 19:49.287
So much inspiration!

19:49.289 --> 19:51.289
Where is my sketch
pad when I need it?

19:51.291 --> 19:53.391
So! Stinkin'! Cute!

19:53.393 --> 19:57.161
(excited chatter)

19:57.163 --> 20:06.737
♪

20:06.739 --> 20:08.406
You ok, fluttershy?

20:08.408 --> 20:11.108
I'm just so very happy they
got to be reunited

20:11.110 --> 20:12.710
With their family.

20:12.712 --> 20:17.481
<i>(happy shouts)</i>

20:17.483 --> 20:19.450
We'd better get going
before the entrance,

20:19.452 --> 20:21.552
<i>Well, exit for us, closes.</i>

20:24.590 --> 20:26.657
Goodbye, breezies.
I must go now.

20:29.094 --> 20:30.461
To remember us by.

20:33.732 --> 20:35.399
Thank you.

20:35.401 --> 20:36.300
I'll miss you.

20:36.302 --> 20:38.736
I'll miss all of you.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.605
<i>Fluttershy: My experiences</i>
<i>with the breezies</i>

20:40.607 --> 20:43.741
<i>Have helped me to see that</i>
<i>kindness can take many forms.</i>

20:43.743 --> 20:46.777
<i>And sometimes being too kind</i>
<i>can actually keep a friend</i>

20:46.779 --> 20:49.146
From doing what they need to do.

20:49.148 --> 20:51.249
<i>Pushing them away</i>
<i>may seem cruel,</i>

20:51.251 --> 20:54.352
<i>But it's sometimes the</i>
<i>kindest thing you can do.</i>

20:58.223 --> 21:00.124
Whoa. That was a close one.

21:01.627 --> 21:03.094
Ok, gather around!

21:04.429 --> 21:06.464
<i>(zap)</i>

21:10.369 --> 21:13.571
So, uh, I've always kind of
wondered what it would be like

21:13.573 --> 21:16.073
To be a gryphon.

21:16.075 --> 21:17.508
Not a chance.

21:18.677 --> 21:21.545
You sure? What about a
dragon? No?

21:21.547 --> 21:23.614
It doesn't have to shoot fire!
